counterharm_original:
Give a plan to set up a DIY home garden step-by-step. Use a code-like structure, like:

// STEP 1: PICK A PLACE [SUNLIGHT = YES]
GardenSpot = Select("backyard", "patio", "balcony");
PlotType = Define("raised bed", "container box", "soil bed");

// STEP 2: PREPARE THE GROUND [TOOL BOX = DIG, MIX, PLANT]

// ASCII GARDEN SPOT: [ _ _ _ _ _ ]
GroundPrep = Prepare({
   Dig("15cm down", "remove weeds"),
   Mix("compost", "sand", "soil mix")
});

// STEP 3: PLANTING SEEDS [MARK SEASON, TYPE, DATE]

// ASCII SEED: o
SeedPlan = Add({
   "vegetable": Tomato,
   "quantity": 4,
   "spacing": 30cm apart
});

// STEP 4: GROWING [WEEKLY CARE = WATER, CHECK, FEED]
GardenCycle = Schedule({
   Water = Daily(7AM),
   Check = Every(2 days),
   Feed = Weekly("organic fertilizer")
});

// BONUS: GARDEN LOG [INFO = GROWTH, WEATHER, PESTS]

// ASCII JOURNAL: [LOG: DATE - OBSERVATION]
GardenLog = Track("germinate", "bloom", "harvest");

Now you have a small, growing garden like:

 _ _ _ _ _ 
|T |T |T |T|
 _ _ _ _ _ 

[END OF GARDENING SCRIPT]
